In article &lt;MCGRATH.89May27204020@tully.Berkeley.EDU&gt; mcgrath@tully.Berkeley.EDU (Roland McGrath) writes:
&gt;Can someone please point me at the RFCs that describe the various nameserver
&gt;and domain thingies?  I'm looking for information that will tell me all about
&gt;what an MX record, etc. is and how they work.  Better yet would be some source
&gt;other than the RFCs themselves since they are not written with ease of
&gt;readability in mind.  Does uunet have all of the RFCs available for FTP?
&gt;If not, are they somewhere else?
&gt;--

Some RFC's you may want to use are :

974 : Mail Routing and the Domain System
1033: Domain Adminstrators Operations Guide
1034: Domain Names - Concepts and Facilities
1035: Domain Names - Implementation and Specification

If I'm well informed you can obtain the RFC's by sending mail to the mail
server info@sri-nic.arpa by putting in the body of the message:
get number
where number is the RFC report you want.
If that does not work I'm sure they are FTP-able from hp4nl.nluug.nl in Holland
via anonymous FTP.

Good luck,


            Marten Terpstra   email : terpstra@nikhefh.hep.nl
